reviewText:
@5 hours:
It takes a little while to understand the game, but thus far it has been some relaxing, casual fun. Having a randomized deck has been a great way to learn the gameplay without stress of building a deck. Although I am not certain, it does seem like eventually you will craft your own decks. I have only played a few hours in campaign mode, and there is PvP and other options to explore.

@11 hours:
I really am enjoying this game. I would highly recommended checking out the the manual and forum help section, as some aspects of the game are not immediately obvious. Honestly, the in-game tutorial should have been much more thorough, but I love this game too much to care. I am at hero level 12, and now I feel like the game is starting to demonstrate its complexity and uniqueness. As you level up, you gain skills, hand slots, mana, etc. which makes it a lot more dynamic. Another player mentioned in his review that this game is simpler than Hearthstone, with which I would disagree. Heartstone is simplified in many regards, such as mana control and diversity of abilities. Battlegrounds at it's core is spell-based rather than minion-based, and in addition to the basic spells (attack, bonus attack, parry, shield, and heal), there are also spells that incorporate the buff area, play area, and discard area. Since my first comments, I have now played Arena mode, which is PvP with a randomized deck. I really enjoy this mode, and I definitely recommend for others to play a couple matches even if their hero is at a low level as the experience rewards are large.
